{
  "video_id": "_tewedUBhAo",
  "title": "What it's like to be the child of immigrants | Michael Rain",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12769.0,
      "end_time": 16215.0,
      "text": "I remember one morning when I was in the third grade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16239.0,
      "end_time": 20870.0,
      "text": "my mom sent me to school with a Ghanaian staple dish called \"fufu.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 20894.0,
      "end_time": 22450.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22475.0,
      "end_time": 26690.0,
      "text": "Fufu is this white ball of starch made of cassava,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26714.0,
      "end_time": 31790.0,
      "text": "and it's served with light soup, which is a dark orange color,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31103.0,
      "end_time": 33337.0,
      "text": "and contains chicken and/or beef."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33859.0,
      "end_time": 35908.0,
      "text": "It's a savory, flavorful dish"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35932.0,
      "end_time": 39155.0,
      "text": "that my mom thought would keep me warm on a cold day."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39509.0,
      "end_time": 42219.0,
      "text": "When I got to lunch and I opened my thermos,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42243.0,
      "end_time": 45320.0,
      "text": "releasing these new smells into the air,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45344.0,
      "end_time": 47763.0,
      "text": "my friends did not react favorably."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47787.0,
      "end_time": 49236.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 49260.0,
      "end_time": 51585.0,
      "text": "\"What's that?\" one of them asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 52122.0,
      "end_time": 54392.0,
      "text": "\"It's fufu,\" I responded."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 54416.0,
      "end_time": 55431.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55455.0,
      "end_time": 58791.0,
      "text": "\"Ew, that smells funny. What's a fufu?\" they asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59642.0,
      "end_time": 61953.0,
      "text": "Their reaction made me lose my appetite."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 62489.0,
      "end_time": 66556.0,
      "text": "I begged my mother to never send me to school with fufu again."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66580.0,
      "end_time": 70860.0,
      "text": "I asked her to make me sandwiches or chicken noodle soup"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 70110.0,
      "end_time": 72868.0,
      "text": "or any of the other foods that my friends were eating."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72892.0,
      "end_time": 74606.0,
      "text": "And this is one of the first times"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74630.0,
      "end_time": 80730.0,
      "text": "I began to notice the distinction between what was unique to my family"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80970.0,
      "end_time": 81960.0,
      "text": "and what was common for everyone else,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 82730.0,
      "end_time": 86560.0,
      "text": "what was Ghanaian and what was African"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 86584.0,
      "end_time": 87879.0,
      "text": "and what was American."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 88645.0,
      "end_time": 90759.0,
      "text": "I'm a first-generation American."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 90784.0,
      "end_time": 92520.0,
      "text": "Both of my parents are immigrants."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 92933.0,
      "end_time": 96798.0,
      "text": "In fact, my father, Gabriel, came to the US almost 50 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 97761.0,
      "end_time": 98985.0,
      "text": "He arrived in New York"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 99900.0,
      "end_time": 102579.0,
      "text": "from a city called Kumasi in a northern region of Ghana,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102603.0,
      "end_time": 103786.0,
      "text": "in West Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 104328.0,
      "end_time": 107713.0,
      "text": "He came for school, earning his bachelor's degree in accounting"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107737.0,
      "end_time": 109640.0,
      "text": "and eventually became an accountant."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110246.0,
      "end_time": 113738.0,
      "text": "My mother, Georgina, joined him years later."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 113762.0,
      "end_time": 115821.0,
      "text": "She had a love of fashion"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 115845.0,
      "end_time": 118872.0,
      "text": "and worked in a sewing factory in lower Manhattan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 118896.0,
      "end_time": 122600.0,
      "text": "until she saved up enough to open her own women's clothing store."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 123527.0,
      "end_time": 125457.0,
      "text": "I consider myself an American"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 126300.0,
      "end_time": 127846.0,
      "text": "and an African"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 127870.0,
      "end_time": 129240.0,
      "text": "and a Ghanaian."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129548.0,
      "end_time": 131946.0,
      "text": "And there's millions of people around the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 131970.0,
      "end_time": 134804.0,
      "text": "who are juggling these different classifications."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135416.0,
      "end_time": 142122.0,
      "text": "They might be Jamaican-Canadians or Korean-Americans or Nigerian-Brits."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 142146.0,
      "end_time": 145188.0,
      "text": "But what makes our stories and experiences different"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 145212.0,
      "end_time": 150484.0,
      "text": "is that we were born and raised in a country different than our parents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 150509.0,
      "end_time": 153658.0,
      "text": "and this can cause us to be misunderstood"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 153682.0,
      "end_time": 156731.0,
      "text": "when being viewed through a narrow lens."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 157672.0,
      "end_time": 161548.0,
      "text": "I grew up in New York, which is home to the largest number of immigrants"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 161572.0,
      "end_time": 163610.0,
      "text": "anywhere in the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 163681.0,
      "end_time": 166624.0,
      "text": "And you would think growing up in a place like New York,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 166648.0,
      "end_time": 170233.0,
      "text": "it would be easy for a first-generation person to find their place."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 170947.0,
      "end_time": 173129.0,
      "text": "But all throughout my childhood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173153.0,
      "end_time": 176583.0,
      "text": "there were these moments that formed my understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 176607.0,
      "end_time": 178578.0,
      "text": "of the different worlds I belonged to."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 179522.0,
      "end_time": 182340.0,
      "text": "When I was in the fifth grade, a student asked me"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 182365.0,
      "end_time": 184719.0,
      "text": "if my family was refugees."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 185386.0,
      "end_time": 187180.0,
      "text": "I didn't know what that word meant."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 187680.0,
      "end_time": 189942.0,
      "text": "He explained to me that his parents told him"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 189966.0,
      "end_time": 193986.0,
      "text": "that refugees are people from Africa who come to the US"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 194100.0,
      "end_time": 196655.0,
      "text": "to escape death, starvation and disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 197452.0,
      "end_time": 200868.0,
      "text": "So I asked my parents, and they laughed a bit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 200892.0,
      "end_time": 204358.0,
      "text": "not because it was funny but because it was a generalization."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 204382.0,
      "end_time": 207299.0,
      "text": "And they assured me that they had enough to eat in Ghana"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 207323.0,
      "end_time": 209763.0,
      "text": "and came to the US willingly."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 209787.0,
      "end_time": 211316.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 211340.0,
      "end_time": 214695.0,
      "text": "These questions became more complex as I got older."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 214719.0,
      "end_time": 216546.0,
      "text": "Junior high school was the first time"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 216570.0,
      "end_time": 219942.0,
      "text": "I went to school with a large number of black American students,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 220845.0,
      "end_time": 224549.0,
      "text": "and many of them couldn't understand why I sounded differently than they did"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 224573.0,
      "end_time": 227606.0,
      "text": "or why my parents seemed different than theirs."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 228336.0,
      "end_time": 230788.0,
      "text": "\"Are you even black?\" a student asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 231788.0,
      "end_time": 233274.0,
      "text": "I mean, I thought I was black."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 233298.0,
      "end_time": 234948.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 234972.0,
      "end_time": 237474.0,
      "text": "I thought my skin complexion settled that."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 237498.0,
      "end_time": 238704.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 238729.0,
      "end_time": 241845.0,
      "text": "I asked my father about it, and he shared his own confusion"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 241869.0,
      "end_time": 245473.0,
      "text": "over the significance of that when he first came to the US."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 246806.0,
      "end_time": 250300.0,
      "text": "He explained to me that, when he was in Ghana, everyone was black,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 250270.0,
      "end_time": 251839.0,
      "text": "so he never thought about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 252768.0,
      "end_time": 254452.0,
      "text": "But in the US, it's a thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 254476.0,
      "end_time": 256618.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 256642.0,
      "end_time": 259704.0,
      "text": "But he would say, \"But you're African."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 259728.0,
      "end_time": 261620.0,
      "text": "Remember that.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 261860.0,
      "end_time": 262598.0,
      "text": "And he would emphasize this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 262622.0,
      "end_time": 267217.0,
      "text": "even though many Africans in the continent would only consider me to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 267241.0,
      "end_time": 268510.0,
      "text": "just an American."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 269584.0,
      "end_time": 272945.0,
      "text": "These misconceptions and complex cultural issues"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 272969.0,
      "end_time": 275117.0,
      "text": "are not just the inquiries of children."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 275141.0,
      "end_time": 277143.0,
      "text": "Adults don't know who immigrants are."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 278160.0,
      "end_time": 280120.0,
      "text": "If we look at current trends,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 280144.0,
      "end_time": 282787.0,
      "text": "if I asked you: What's the fastest-growing"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 282811.0,
      "end_time": 285390.0,
      "text": "immigrant demographic in the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 285415.0,
      "end_time": 286803.0,
      "text": "who would you think it was?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 287249.0,
      "end_time": 289637.0,
      "text": "Nine out of 10 people tell me it's Latinos,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 289661.0,
      "end_time": 291740.0,
      "text": "but it's actually African immigrants."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 292341.0,
      "end_time": 293891.0,
      "text": "How about in academics?"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 294329.0,
      "end_time": 297214.0,
      "text": "What's the most educated immigrant demographic?"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 297754.0,
      "end_time": 301993.0,
      "text": "A lot of people presume it to be Asians, but it's actually African immigrants."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 302170.0,
      "end_time": 303673.0,
      "text": "Even in matters of policy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 304176.0,
      "end_time": 306596.0,
      "text": "did you know that three out of the eight countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 306620.0,
      "end_time": 308190.0,
      "text": "in the so-called \"travel ban\""
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 308430.0,
      "end_time": 309296.0,
      "text": "are African countries?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 309859.0,
      "end_time": 314490.0,
      "text": "A lot of people assume those targeted Muslims only live in the Middle East,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 314740.0,
      "end_time": 316669.0,
      "text": "but a lot of those banned people are Africans."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 317334.0,
      "end_time": 322116.0,
      "text": "So on these issues of education and policy and religion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 322140.0,
      "end_time": 325594.0,
      "text": "a lot of things we presume about immigrants are incorrect."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 326634.0,
      "end_time": 331764.0,
      "text": "Even if we look at something like workplace diversity and inclusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 331788.0,
      "end_time": 334822.0,
      "text": "if I asked you what gender-ethnicity combination"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 334846.0,
      "end_time": 338854.0,
      "text": "is least likely to be promoted to senior managerial positions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 338878.0,
      "end_time": 340308.0,
      "text": "who would you think it was?"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 340831.0,
      "end_time": 342626.0,
      "text": "The answer is not Africans this time."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 342650.0,
      "end_time": 343775.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 343800.0,
      "end_time": 346760.0,
      "text": "And it's not black women or men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 346100.0,
      "end_time": 348516.0,
      "text": "and it's not Latin women or men."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 348540.0,
      "end_time": 351719.0,
      "text": "It's Asian women who are least likely to be promoted."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 353680.0,
      "end_time": 356248.0,
      "text": "Capturing these stories and issues is part of my work"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 356272.0,
      "end_time": 358105.0,
      "text": "as a digital storyteller"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 358129.0,
      "end_time": 361399.0,
      "text": "that uses tech to make it easier for people to find these stories."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 362790.0,
      "end_time": 367836.0,
      "text": "This year, I launched an online gallery of portraits and firsthand accounts"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 367860.0,
      "end_time": 369717.0,
      "text": "for a project called Enodi."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 370534.0,
      "end_time": 376253.0,
      "text": "The goal of Enodi is to highlight first-generation immigrants just like me"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 376277.0,
      "end_time": 380240.0,
      "text": "who carry this kinship for the countries we grew up in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 381810.0,
      "end_time": 383430.0,
      "text": "for the countries of origin"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 384136.0,
      "end_time": 386374.0,
      "text": "and for this concept called \"blackness.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 387581.0,
      "end_time": 392461.0,
      "text": "I created this space to be a cyberhome for many of us who are misunderstood"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 392485.0,
      "end_time": 394817.0,
      "text": "in our different home countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 395521.0,
      "end_time": 397338.0,
      "text": "There are millions of Enodis"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 397362.0,
      "end_time": 400810.0,
      "text": "who use hyphens to connect their countries of origin"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 400105.0,
      "end_time": 403266.0,
      "text": "with their various homes in the US"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 403290.0,
      "end_time": 406620.0,
      "text": "or Canada or Britain or Germany."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 407195.0,
      "end_time": 410980.0,
      "text": "In fact, many people you might know are Enodi."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 410738.0,
      "end_time": 413586.0,
      "text": "Actors Issa Rae and Idris Elba are Enodi."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 413995.0,
      "end_time": 415314.0,
      "text": "Colin Powell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 415338.0,
      "end_time": 417917.0,
      "text": "former Attorney General Eric Holder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 417941.0,
      "end_time": 420436.0,
      "text": "former President of the United States, Barack Obama,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 420461.0,
      "end_time": 423393.0,
      "text": "are all the children of African or Caribbean immigrants."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 423842.0,
      "end_time": 425724.0,
      "text": "But how much do you know about us?"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 426694.0,
      "end_time": 430413.0,
      "text": "This complicated navigation"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 430437.0,
      "end_time": 434701.0,
      "text": "is not just the experience of first-generation folks."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 435701.0,
      "end_time": 437699.0,
      "text": "We're so intertwined"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 437723.0,
      "end_time": 442676.0,
      "text": "in the lives and culture of people in North America and Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 442700.0,
      "end_time": 445409.0,
      "text": "that you might be surprised how critical we are"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 445434.0,
      "end_time": 447425.0,
      "text": "to your histories and future."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 448153.0,
      "end_time": 450431.0,
      "text": "So, engage us in conversation;"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 451260.0,
      "end_time": 453128.0,
      "text": "discover who immigrants actually are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 453152.0,
      "end_time": 456298.0,
      "text": "and see us apart from characterizations"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 456322.0,
      "end_time": 458204.0,
      "text": "or limited media narratives"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 458228.0,
      "end_time": 460589.0,
      "text": "or even who we might appear to be."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 461336.0,
      "end_time": 464371.0,
      "text": "We're walking melting pots of culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 464395.0,
      "end_time": 467645.0,
      "text": "and if something in that pot smells new or different to you --"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 467669.0,
      "end_time": 469764.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 469788.0,
      "end_time": 471378.0,
      "text": "don't turn up your nose."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 472430.0,
      "end_time": 473267.0,
      "text": "Ask us to share."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 473865.0,
      "end_time": 475580.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 475820.0,
      "end_time": 480123.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}